{"type":"message","id":"dd4fd0c0","parentId":"1af3c2dd","timestamp":"2026-03-04T19:25:42.797Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to add a Telegram channel (-1003812821838) to OpenClaw for receiving and responding to messages. This is a group/channel chat (the -100 prefix indicates a Telegram group/channel ID).\n\nTo add a Telegram channel to OpenClaw, I need to configure it. Let me check the OpenClaw configuration to see how to add a new channel.\n\nActually, looking at the runtime metadata, I see the current channel is \"telegram\" with chat_id \"1734128684\" (a direct chat). The user wants to add a different Telegram chat -1003812821838.\n\nI should look at the OpenClaw config to see how to add a new channel. Let me check what configuration options are available.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dvlbvsxovq68_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway config --help 2>&1 || cat /etc/openclaw/config.yaml 2>/dev/null || cat ~/.openclaw/config.yaml 2>/dev/null || ls -la ~/.openclaw/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5:free","usage":{"input":12233,"output":220,"cacheRead":1089,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13542,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772652336550}}
